main event: A civilian observed a single unidentified object in Glendale, Pennsylvania on November 20, 1966 around 9:05 PM.
interesting points: The object was observed for a total duration of 10 minutes.
The witness was certain about the time of observation.
The object did not move in any specific course, with no motion noted.
No photographs were taken of the object.
The witness estimated the distance to the object to be approximately 21,000 feet away.
